nts1.d:
Malibu is a French electronic musician whose work sails between ambient and ethereal music.
Forever inspired by soft reverbed vocals and melodious chord progressions, Malibu’s music is an immersive nostalgic journey in a sea of synthetic strings and choirs.

nts1.n: NTS GUIDE TO: MID-WESTERN '90S SPACE & POST ROCK (R)
nts1.d: Many of these bands existed at the intersection of Space Rock, Shoegaze & Psychedelia. Releasing on labels such as Kranky, Burnt Hair & Mind Expansion these bands carved out a unique but small scene in places such as Michigan and Illinois in the mid - late 90's. Today many of these bands still aren't well known, enjoy a 2 hour selection of their recordings.
Ziggy Devriendt is the DJ behind Nosedrip. Tune in once a month for an expert selection of any or all of the following: new age, new wave, French psych, minimal synth, post-punk and a whole lot else…
Basma shares songs and stories from passings through Khartoum and beyond.
Explorations in music from Ruth Tafébé a.k.a The Afrosoulmessenger.

A unique dip into the musical history of Ukraine with archival label Shukai, journeying back to the ‘90s, playing music from documentaries, sci-fi films, obscure cartoons and late-night music programming, curated by Dmytro Nikolaienko, Dmytro Prutkin and Alec Tsapenko.
From the host: "Step inside the sonic laboratory of Soviet Ukraine’s Kyivnaukfilm (Eng: Kyiv Science Film, active years 1941-1993) studio — a workshop where composers and sound designers crafted scores for documentary, science, education, and animation films. From eerie synth textures to inventive tape collages, these rare recordings (1967–1990) reveal a secret world of avant-garde music created under censorship yet brimming with experiments."

Did the Oracle stir in her sleep? Did Apollo look up from his lyre and see this brilliant boy pass by?
Oracle was commissioned by La Becque Résidence d’artistes as part of Modern Nature 2025. It is dedicated with love and thanks to Vanessa Cimorelli, Luc Meier, all at La Becque and especially to Jane Wildgoose, our oracle.

Tearooms in post-revolution Czechoslovakia symbolised places through which new spiritualities were flowing, and the influx of largely uncharted ways of life closely intertwined with new age, ambient, folk and minimalism. With their minds altered thanks to smuggled records by Fripp & Eno or Steve Reich, this loose network of musicians had begun composing meditative music, using loops and handmade instruments, with a different sensibility. Compared to the boisterous Zappa-adjacent and booze-soaked underground movement, which was led by Plastic People of the Universe and provoked the state authorities, this music was meant instead for tea rooms and spiritual sites like churches or monasteries, as if occupying some place where time flows anticlockwise. Music journalist Pavel Klusák dubbed this 1990s scene a “tearoom alternative”. Experimental folk singer Oldřich Janota, Jaroslav Kořán’s various ensembles like Modrá or Orloj Snivců (The Horologe of Dreamers) or Irena and Vojtěch Havlovi were drawn by the light and composed music that didn’t match the fast pace of newly imported capitalism.
Mix created by: Miloš Hroch

nts2.d: The glitchy blips and bops of Indietronica always remind me of how organic music is and how rhythm and melody shape our lives without us realizing. Enjoy this one hour Indietronica mix to find peace in knowing that music is everywhere around us ☆
For when you need to soften the edges.

nts2.n: HEAVEN IS A FRIEND, EARTH IS A GOSSIP W/ AR

nts2.d: Exploring peace not as the absence of struggle, but as the act of turning towards what grounds, supports, and connects us: bright sun, a nice long sigh, music, a kiss beneath an apple tree, a prayer, falling snow, a caring confidant.

nts2.n: Major 7th, Love, and Happiness w/ treasure token
nts2.d: I’ve always felt that certain songs have a special relaxing, pensive sound to them, like a musical sigh. At some point I learned that there’s a name for that sound: the major 7th chord. This is a mix of songs with major 7ths and their musical modes, to bring you that inner peace we all need.

"These are the two paths: liquid and sound," writes poet Lisa Robertson. These tracks float and dive deep and float again. Soft ropes into the heart; everything dissolves like a calm gem around the head.
An hour of stillness and movement featuring a selection of ambient, jazz, electronic and folk woven with readings of Wendell Berry poems. Inspired by nature.

nts2.n: Dialogue for Peace w/ DJ IORI
nts2.d: Behind the light lies darkness. From ancient times to the present, conflict and tragedy have never ceased. In this work, I wanted to depict naked, destitute people engaged in quiet dialogue about love, freedom, dignity, and peace, whether in a deep forest, on a vast desert, or under a starry sky.
Peace found through fragmented melodies and wisps of rhythmic patterns. A hazy journey through familiar sounds that warm the soul and ease the mind. Enjoy.

nts2.n: The Shake It Show w/ Bomba Brown
nts2.d: An audio postcard, a love letter from the Daliang Mountains to the world. During my artist residency with the Wilderhaven Project, I learned about the Hulusheng and indigenous weaving practices from Ms. Xiong and the Dechang Lisu Heritagers.  I collected field recordings on the mountain, at the loom, the markets, tea houses, mahjong houses, and in the forest while foraging mushrooms.  I listened to music while sewing each day, and those songs are woven in as well.  I was in a practice of deep listening to rest, liberation, and what sounds slow down the heart with my sister Woostalila.
Blocking out, reducing, getting rid of things in the process of getting some quietude - from solemn, through blissful to quite facetious. A bit of lonely dwelling and mood swings very much included.
Solemn in many ways. Some favorite sounds. They help maintain the ease.

The shore, once bustling with life, now lies cold and deserted. The summer residents have long gone, leaving a quiet, melancholic peace in their wake. A distantly familiar soundtrack soaked in digital synths and electric pianos washes in with the waves.
A kid in in rural Czechia spinning burned CDs from a family friend and games from the sales bin

subtle.d:
DJ & Producer, B-Say has been a Subtle resident DJ for over 3 years.

His radio shows tend to focus on the 140 bass music scene and aims to showcase unreleased/forthcoming music from upcoming artists, as well as premiering his own unreleased material. 

More recently B-Say has ventured out from solely DJ'ing Dubstep, with his bi-monthly 'Dub & Steppers Show' which he uses to premier his own productions.

Slick is a London-based Producer and DJ combining the sounds of Grime and Drill.
Expect sets to span from sparse wave and weightless to classic NY and UK Drill, with everything in between
J:KENZO is a producer and record label owner (Artikal Music & Lion Charge) from the UK. Known for his minimalistic dark tribal sound in the both the dubstep and drum and bass scenes since 2006.

DJ and radio producer TILDA will be live from the studio to kick off your weekend. She’ll cover all corners of electronic music as well as showcasing unmissable new tracks & chatting about motives for the weekend. 

Each month TILDA will be closing the show with a signature mix.

Live & Direct is the show that promises to make you dance and make you laugh, with your fave tunes that make you go 'Rahhh ain't hear this in time' and all the cheesy jokes from me, Hannah :) Lock in for the sickest guests and the most relatable stories about daily slips and hilarious situations I find myself in.

Following his widely acclaimed breakout moment winning the 2013 DMC World Online Championships, Jon1st quickly built an international reputation as a ‘DJ’s DJ’. Not only proving himself as one of the world’s most diverse and musical turntablists, Jon also established himself as an on the pulse club DJ mixing across the alternative bass music spectrum and as an in demand live performer around the world, as well as recording acclaimed guest mixes for everyone from DJ Mag to Boiler Room to Ninja Tune’s Solid Steel to Mary Anne Hobbs to Keep Hush.

Established in 2013, eatmybeat is a hybrid record label & club brand that was brought together by a group of friends with a passion for electronic music and building community. With diverse tastes, they support and champion the underground bass music scene through events and releases on the label. Refusing to be pigeonholed into a specific sound, they showcase everything from hip-hop, bass & breaks, through to techno, jungle, dubstep and grime. As long as it's tasty and full fat, you best believe eatmybeat are snacking on it.
Born in Sunderland, based in London, Kitschko's productions and selections display a deep appreciation of UK club culture, and an affinity for late night, introspective sounds.

As a drummer since childhood, Chacho has always had an insatiable appetite for new and unique beats.
Combining his love of global percussion, dark grooves and deeper low end frequencies, 
his sets feature a blend of dubstep, grime, garage, breaks, hip hop and other flavours from around the world.
